messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /notifications/{notificationId}
  - Rationale: The deleteNotification method is mapped with @RequestMapping(value="/notifications/{notificationId}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE), and there is no class-level prefix, so the full path is exactly /notifications/{notificationId}.

- Are all HTTP methods acceptable? No
  - Rationale: Only DELETE and PUT are mapped for this path. No other methods are defined for this endpoint.

- HEAD: Not acceptable
  - Rationale: There is no HEAD mapping for this path in the code; only DELETE and PUT are defined.

- POST: Not acceptable
  - Rationale: There is no POST mapping for this path in the code.

- OPTIONS: Not acceptable
  - Rationale: There is no explicit OPTIONS mapping for this path in the code.

- TRACE: Not acceptable
  - Rationale: There is no TRACE mapping for this path in the code.

- GET: Not acceptable
  - Rationale: There is no GET mapping for this path in the code.

- PUT: Acceptable
  - Rationale: The readNotification method is mapped to this path with method = RequestMethod.PUT, so PUT is supported for marking a notification as read.

- DELETE: Acceptable
  - Rationale: The deleteNotification method is mapped to this path with method = RequestMethod.DELETE, so DELETE is supported for removing a notification.

- PATCH: Not acceptable
  - Rationale: There is no PATCH mapping for this path in the code.

Explanation:
- The endpoint in question handles /notifications/{notificationId} for DELETE (deleteNotification) and PUT (readNotification). Since the class does not declare a broader @RequestMapping prefix, the path is exactly /notifications/{notificationId}. Only the HTTP methods DELETE and PUT are implemented for this path; all other methods are not defined in this controller for this path. Therefore, only DELETE and PUT are acceptable according to the code. HEAD/POST/OPTIONS/TRACE/GET/PATCH are not supported by direct mappings in this code.
